value: Breeds in northern Siberia from the Yalmal Peninsula and the Yenessei River (overlapping the range of P. a. apricaria), east to western Alaska on the shores of Kotzebue Sound and Bering Sea; south in eastern Siberia to the Stanovoi Mountains and Kamchatka. Winters in eastern India, southern Cliina, Indo-Cliinese countries, Malay Arcliipelago, Oceania, Australia and the Hawaiian Islands; straggles west to East Africa and east to the Pacific coast of North America.

Vagrant: mainly coast: E half of continent Sudan - South Africa.

Grassy tundra, usually in areas at lower elevation, in denser and taller vegetative cover than [i]P. dominica[/i] (breeding); pastures, plowed fields, and less often mudflats, beaches, and bare shores of lakes (nonbreeding).
breeds in drier parts of tundra:shrub tundra, rarely forest tundra, & on stony, well-drained upland with moss & lichens;montane tundra in Chukotski & Koryakski highlands;winters coastal areas
